  "why": "The paper evaluates semantic image mutations against standard semantic-segmentation perception models (Cityscapes benchmark SUTs) and reports failures as decreases in segmentation accuracy (percentage-point drops in IoU / “inconsistencies” between expected and predicted interpretations). The experiments and oracle are framed around pixel-labeling accuracy and class misclassification (robustness-related errors). The paper does not target or evaluate models that are described as having explicit safety, policy, or security safeguards, nor does it empirically demonstrate bypassing any such safeguards to induce prohibited or safety-violating behavior. Therefore the most severe demonstrated failure class in the paper is robustness-related mispredictions (Low).",
